ContactDetailsForListDuplicatesCriteriaM.title:
- CRITERIA_MATCH_TYPE_UNKNOWN: preserved for error/unknown state
 - CRITERIA_MATCH_TYPE_PHONE_NUMBER: will match a dupe if contact phone number matches
 - CRITERIA_MATCH_TYPE_EMAIL: will match a dupe if contact email matches
 - CRITERIA_MATCH_TYPE_PHONE_NUMBER_AND_EMAIL: will match a dupe if BOTH contact phonenumber AND contact email match
 - CRITERIA_MATCH_TYPE_PHONENUMBER_OR_EMAIL: will match a dupe if EITHER contact phonenumber OR contact email match

editionId.title:
To preserve backwards compatibility, an edition_id of `""` won't be used in the filter. For apps that have an edition of `""` that you want to filter specifically for
you can use the value of `default` and that will be changed to `""` when doing the query. Unfotunately edition_id is not supported when querying for an account status of
disabled

expiredInDays.description: Indicates the result set should include accounts with LD that has expired in the last N days.

v1ForeignKey.description:
A Foreign Key Constraint represents a model stored in another service.
Existence of a Foreign Key Constraint will prevent deleting an account group.
Values of the Foreign Key do not have any meaning to this service, but should be meaningful to a client.

key.description:
A string representation primary key of the used to identify the row that references the account group.
It is up to the client to determine how composite keys are stored as a string.

kind.description: If using vstore, the vstore kind of the other model that references the account group. Otherwise identifier to help identify the source.
